Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on resource allocation in a machine-to-machine enabled cellular network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with power control and time allocation, which are key concepts in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves optimization of a system with multiple components, which can be categorized under systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses nonorthogonal multiple access (NOMA) and time division multiple access (TDMA), which are commonly used in multimedia communication systems. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper involves distributed resource allocation in a cellular network, which can be categorized under distributed computing.
